
    Charlottesville driver Alex Fields Jr found guilty of murder

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 Reuters
                
            
            
            Image caption
                
                    Alex Fields Jr (l) was pictured taking part in the Unite the Right rally in Charlottesville, Virginia
                
            A man who drove his car into a crowd of protesters in Virginia, killing a woman, has been found guilty of murder.Alex Fields Jr, a 21-year-old described as a white supremacist, was on trial over the incident in Charlottesville in August 2017.Heather Heyer, 32, died when the car hit a group of people protesting against a white nationalist rally.Mr Fields's lawyers had insisted he acted out of fear for his own safety. He will be sentenced at a later date.
            

